TRAGEDY struck on Friday when Mbhoni Ngobeni went missing after he and a friend went for a swim at a local river.Ntshunxeko Nyathi (9) and Mbhoni Ngobeni (9) went to Nwandlamharhi River in Songeni outside Thulamahashe near Bushbuckridge, Mpumalanga, to cool themselves down.Little did they know the day would end on a bad note.While they were in the river Mbhoni suddenly struggled to stay afloat. Some members of the community believe the river is full of crocodiles.Police spokesman Colonel John Ngwenya said a team of divers was called in to find the boy. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjssamkX2pakWdEnEX8kwgKUwtlsL8SJmPmSaeuDsAexJurjXBPBWfPoiylnEF2fvIoA6NqVcauCytwbHpHwXDWSbEZgx9soKyOAomd0nRHcD0hoINMGPmTvHS46ClS8cxcplvX2XHDq--X2COSRIVftc7mzv_hPAqRcTggnymJkZx_oXqvLgJ2Gn4sfdLI1thr7MQ_AyDa8gwZ_fKkXfjppDTjcGvZ6PylVSGipbY0X561CVPJ6Pr8EdBPy9kBHGEsZPNemhNZNqQqBoMHA3yx9JTFoCyUQ\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzEPHe-UqZSYWEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
